      <akn:section eId="sec_27_103">
        <akn:num>27-103</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Criminal proceedings.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_27-103_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>The recovery of damages from the alleged offender shall not prohibit criminal prosecution of the alleged offender.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_27-103_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>The recovery of civil damages by a merchant or a finding of liability under this chapter shall not be admissible in a criminal proceeding.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_27-103_c">
      <akn:num>(c)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>A conviction or plea of guilty of fraud, shoplifting, or theft is not a prerequisite to the maintenance of a civil action authorized by this chapter.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
      </akn:section>
